11. O-O-O Qa5! {[%csl Ga2]} { Black starts attacking at once. With opposite castling time is of paramount importance. } ( { Banzea proposed the very original pawn sacrifice } 11...f5!? { . The idea is that after } 12.Bxf5 Nf6 { The knight is excellent on f6 and the white bishop on e3 is rather clumsy. This gives Black adequate positional compensation for the pawn - and the engine agrees and calls it equal!

The line is completely fresh, so there are few games available. My editor - who was also editor on the Banzea course! - tried it. Let's see what happened: } 13.Bxc8 Rxc8 14.Rde1 Ng4! 15.Ng3 Bxg3 16.hxg3 Nxe3 { 16...Qd5! was perhaps even stronger. } 17.Rxe3 Rxe3 18.fxe3 Qg5 19.Qf2 Re8 20.Re1 Re4! { followed by ...Rg4 and ...Rxg3, when Black regained the pawn with some advantage, Veselic-Novak, Slovenia 2023.

