[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Schandorff's Caro-Kann"]
[White "8) Advance Variation: 4.c3"]
[Black "Advance 4.c3 with 5.Be3"]
[Date "2024.10.21"]
[Result "*"]
[ECO "B12"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/42092475"]

1. e4 c6 
2. d4 d5 
3. e5 c5 
4. c3 {[%csl Gc3,Gd4,Ge5]} ( { With this move, White secures the centre and builds a strong foundation. This line is probably somewhat underestimated. For some reason, most white players prefer piece play and more forcing lines when confronted with 3...c5!?. Playing positionally with } 4.c3 { definitely has its merits, though. If Black answers } 4...e6 { , a well-known position from the French is on the board - but with a tempo more for White!

Of course, we have no intention of playing that way. On the contrary, Black hopes to exploit the fact that the c8-h3 diagonal is not closed yet, which means it's possible to develop the light-squared bishop outside the pawn chain. You have to be a little careful, though, because the bishop might become a target. } ) Nc6 {[%mdl 32768]} 
5. Be3 {[%csl Gd4]} ( { For now we leave the bishop on c8. On f5 it might be vulnerable, and we dream of - or kind of expect - that White will play the natural } 5.Nf3 { , when we can go } 5...Bg4 { , pinning the knight and putting extra pressure on d4 that way.

In this position, White has tried several moves. 5.Nf3 is just one of them! } ) { White strengthens the d4-point and gets the bishop out. It is rather passive on e3, though. } Qb6 {[%csl Gb2]} { Other moves are possible, but I like to start playing on the queenside in order to distract White. } 
6. Qd2 ( 6.b3 { weakens more than it helps. } 6...cxd4 7.cxd4 Bf5 { is good for Black. The white knight will be unstable on c3 compared to the mainline of 5.Be3. } ) cxd4 { You could postpone this exchange, but now the play is very straightforward. } 
7. cxd4 Bf5 { The bishop comes out. } 
8. Nc3 e6 
9. Nf3 ( 9.a3 { to prevent ...Bb4 can be met by } 9...Rc8 $146 10.Nf3 Bg4! 11.Be2 Nge7 { followed by ...Nf5 with good play. } ) Bb4 
10. Be2 Nge7 { Black gets all pieces out. } 
11. O-O O-O 
12.-- ( { The position is balanced. An important detail is } 12.Nh4 h6 $146 ! { Black is ready to move the bishop and } 13.Nxf5 Nxf5 { is at least equal. } )
*

