[ECO "B12"]
[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/41961674"]

1. e4 c6 
2. d4 d5 
3. e5 c5 
4. c3 {[%csl Gc3,Gd4,Ge5]} ( { With this move, White secures the centre and builds a strong foundation. This line is probably somewhat underestimated. For some reason, most white players prefer piece play and more forcing lines when confronted with 3...c5!?. Playing positionally with } 4.c3 { definitely has its merits, though. If Black answers } 4...e6 { , a well-known position from the French is on the board - but with a tempo more for White!

Of course, we have no intention of playing that way. On the contrary, Black hopes to exploit the fact that the c8-h3 diagonal is not closed yet, which means it's possible to develop the light-squared bishop outside the pawn chain. You have to be a little careful, though, because the bishop might become a target. } ) Nc6 
5. Ne2 ( { For now we leave the bishop on c8. On f5 it might be vulnerable, and we dream of - or kind of expect - that White will play the natural } 5.Nf3 { , when we can go } 5...Bg4 { , pinning the knight and putting extra pressure on d4 that way.

In this position, White has tried several moves. 5.Nf3 is just one of them! } ) ( { A strange move. It is easy to underestimate such clumsy looking ideas, but the knight is not forced to remain on e2 and at least White avoids the pin after } 5.Nf3 Bg4 { . } ) Bd7!? {[%mdl 32768]} ( { OK, we respond with an unusual move of our own. I believe we can get a superb version of the French because the knight is misplaced on e2. It was also possible to start with } 5...e6 { . } ) 
6. Nd2 cxd4 ( 6...e6 7.Nf3 { gives White an improved version of the 6.f4 line. } ) 
7. cxd4 Qa5!? {[%cal Ga5e1]} { A cool novelty. The d2-knight is pinned so White can't play Nf3. } 
8. g3 Rc8 
9. Bg2 Bg4! {[%cal Gg4d1,Ga5e1,Gc6d4]} { This is why we waited a little with the move e6! Suddenly the bishop joins the battle, pinning the other knight and attacking d4. } 
10. f3 Bd7 {[%cal Ga5b6][%csl Gd4]} { Black has a good French. Next comes ...Qb6 with annoying pressure on d4. } 
