11. Be2 Bd6 
12. Bxd6 Qxd6 {[%csl Gf4]} { Positionally Black is fine, but play can quickly become quite sharp. } 
13. O-O O-O-O!? {[%mdl 32768]} {[%cal Gg6f4,Gg7g5,Gh5h4,Gd8g8,Gg5g4]} { Black has good play. It is rare that I recommend castling long in this structure. Here it is well founded, because we are already ready to launch a strong attack on the white king with moves like ...Nf4, ...g5, ...h4 and ...g4. We might just mate our opponent! } 
